vulnerability.name: USN-7648-1
vulnerability.description: It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled certain hostnames containing null characters. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to bypass certain hostname validation checks. (CVE-2025-1220)  It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled the pgsql and pdo_pgsql escaping functions. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause PHP to crash, resulting in a denial of service. (CVE-2025-1735)  It was discovered that PHP incorrectly handled parsing certain XML data in SOAP extensions. A remote attacker could possibly use this issue to cause PHP to crash, resulting in a denial of service. (CVE-2025-6491)

statements.status_notes: Several security issues were fixed in PHP.
